
Yum

yum provides '*/vimdiff'
	find packages with given filename

yum list available package-name --listavailable
	show all versions of a package


sudo yum -y -v groupinstall "C Development Tools and Libraries"
    Install package group

yum group info "C Development Tools and Libraries"
    Show packages in group


repoquery --whatrequires <pkg>
	show packages depending on pkg


Dnf

Repo management
    repolist [all]
        list enabled [all] repos

Packages - can use globbing in pkg name
    search <pkg>  shows & searches by name, description
    info <pkg>    shows details
    list [<pkg>]
                show pkg version, repo, if installed or available
                if no pkg, lists installed then avail packages
                does not sync metadata
    list [installed | available]
                list all available and installed [just installed | avail & not installed]

    install, reinstall, remove, downgrade
    options:
        --exclude <pkg>         don't install a dependency
        --enablerepo <repo>     install pkg from a repo
        --disable <repo>



Package Groups
    grouplist

History
    list
        recent
        upgrade <pkg>       avail upgrades for pkg
        userinstalled       manually installed pkgs
    undo
    rollback

Other
    autoremove  uninstall orphan pkgs
    clean all   clear package cache



